Description: Fragment of a small seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration with a partly glossy surface. The rear shows a convex surface like from a leather bag and perpendicular to this the impression of a turned cord with a width of 0.4 cm in the break. The front has a small flat area on which part of an oval scarab-like seal-impression is preserved, next to it another impression of a turned cord with a width of 0.45 cm. the seal-impression shows a thin circumferential line. In the centre a cartouche with Mn-kheper-R' and on each side of a small winged scarab rotated with its heads towards the cartouche. Probably identical seal on EA86819, EA86894 and EA86899.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
